article.headline: Tulane 73, Marshall 65
article.story: HUNTINGTON, W.Va. (AP) -- David Gomez scored six of his eight points during a 13-5 run to end the game, leading Tulane to a 73-65 win over Marshall on Saturday night. Chris Moore and Daniel Puckett scored 17 points apiece to lead Tulane (13-11, 6-6 Conference USA). Donnie Stith added 10 points. Markel Humphrey and Mark Dorris had 15 points apiece for Marshall (10-16, 5-7). Moore made two free throws to give Tulane the lead for good and hit a 3-pointer a minute later to put the Green Wave ahead 60-56 with 4:26 remaining in the game. Marshall trimmed the deficit to 61-60 with 2:44 left after two Dorris free throws before Tulane took over. Stith started the run with a jumper with 2:20 left and Gomez hit a jumper a minute later.
